{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":544,"text":"By 2010, Detroit had become the poster child"},{"time":3571,"text":"for an American city in crisis."},{"time":5712,"text":"There was a housing collapse,"},{"time":7584,"text":"an auto industry collapse,"},{"time":9542,"text":"and the population had plummeted by 25 percent"},{"time":12094,"text":"between 2000 and 2010,"},{"time":14516,"text":"and many people were beginning to write it off,"},{"time":16733,"text":"as it had topped the list of American shrinking cities."},{"time":20459,"text":"By 2010, I had also been asked by"},{"time":22846,"text":"the Kresge Foundation and the city of Detroit"},{"time":25046,"text":"to join them in leading a citywide planning process"},{"time":28300,"text":"for the city to create a shared vision for its future."},{"time":31774,"text":"I come to this work"},{"time":33245,"text":"as an architect and an urban planner,"},{"time":35062,"text":"and I've spent my career working\nin other contested cities,"},{"time":37668,"text":"like Chicago, my hometown;"},{"time":39524,"text":"Harlem, which is my current home;"},{"time":41530,"text":"Washington, D.C.; and Newark, New Jersey."},{"time":44556,"text":"All of these cities, to me, still had a number"},{"time":46936,"text":"of unresolved issues related to urban justice,"},{"time":49772,"text":"issues of equity, inclusion and access."}]},{"cues":[{"time":54124,"text":"Now by 2010, as well,"},{"time":56187,"text":"popular design magazines were also beginning"},{"time":58202,"text":"to take a closer look at cities like Detroit,"},{"time":60915,"text":"and devoting whole issues to \"fixing the city.\""},{"time":64552,"text":"I was asked by a good friend, Fred Bernstein,"},{"time":66928,"text":"to do an interview for the October issue"},{"time":68903,"text":"of Architect magazine,"},{"time":70554,"text":"and he and I kind of had a good chuckle"},{"time":72209,"text":"when we saw the magazine released with the title,"},{"time":75425,"text":"\"Can This Planner Save Detroit?\""},{"time":78311,"text":"So I'm smiling with a little bit\nof embarrassment right now,"},{"time":81186,"text":"because obviously, it's completely absurd"},{"time":83593,"text":"that a single person, let alone a planner,"},{"time":85565,"text":"could save a city."},{"time":87023,"text":"But I'm also smiling because I thought it represented"},{"time":89524,"text":"a sense of hopefulness that our profession"},{"time":92158,"text":"could play a role in helping the city to think about"},{"time":95076,"text":"how it would recover from its severe crisis."},{"time":99140,"text":"So I'd like to spend a little bit of time this afternoon"},{"time":101412,"text":"and tell you a little bit about our process"},{"time":103093,"text":"for fixing the city, a little bit about Detroit,"},{"time":105769,"text":"and I want to do that through\nthe voices of Detroiters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":108883,"text":"So we began our process in September of 2010."},{"time":111951,"text":"It's just after a special mayoral election,"},{"time":114880,"text":"and word has gotten out that there is going to be"},{"time":116921,"text":"this citywide planning process,"},{"time":118465,"text":"which brings a lot of anxiety and fears"},{"time":120814,"text":"among Detroiters."},{"time":122602,"text":"We had planned to hold a number\nof community meetings in rooms like this"},{"time":126842,"text":"to introduce the planning process,"},{"time":129226,"text":"and people came out from all over the city,"},{"time":131222,"text":"including areas that were stable neighborhoods,"},{"time":134073,"text":"as well as areas that were beginning to see"},{"time":135849,"text":"a lot of vacancy."},{"time":137843,"text":"And most of our audience was representative"},{"time":139941,"text":"of the 82 percent African-American population"},{"time":142494,"text":"in the city at that time."},{"time":144759,"text":"So obviously, we have a Q&amp;A portion of our program,"},{"time":148247,"text":"and people line up to mics to ask questions."},{"time":151144,"text":"Many of them step very firmly to the mic,"},{"time":153903,"text":"put their hands across their chest, and go,"},{"time":156751,"text":"\"I know you people are trying to\nmove me out of my house, right?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":160230,"text":"So that question is really powerful,"},{"time":162549,"text":"and it was certainly powerful to us in the moment,"},{"time":165762,"text":"when you connect it to the stories"},{"time":167871,"text":"that some Detroiters had,"},{"time":169258,"text":"and actually a lot of African-Americans'"},{"time":171464,"text":"families have had"},{"time":172921,"text":"that are living in Midwestern cities like Detroit."},{"time":176652,"text":"Many of them told us the stories about"},{"time":178987,"text":"how they came to own their home"},{"time":180447,"text":"through their grandparents or great-grandparents,"},{"time":182611,"text":"who were one of 1.6 million people who migrated"},{"time":185485,"text":"from the rural South to the industrial North,"},{"time":188178,"text":"as depicted in this painting by Jacob Lawrence,"},{"time":190526,"text":"\"The Great Migration.\""},{"time":192152,"text":"They came to Detroit for a better way of life."},{"time":195395,"text":"Many found work in the automobile industry,"},{"time":197999,"text":"the Ford Motor Company, as depicted in this mural"},{"time":200400,"text":"by Diego Rivera in the Detroit Institute of Art."},{"time":204455,"text":"The fruits of their labors would afford them a home,"},{"time":207430,"text":"for many the first piece of property\nthat they would ever know,"},{"time":210311,"text":"and a community with other first-time"},{"time":212174,"text":"African-American home buyers."},{"time":214303,"text":"The first couple of decades of their life in the North"},{"time":216683,"text":"is quite well, up until about 1950,"},{"time":219727,"text":"which coincides with the city's peak population"},{"time":222335,"text":"at 1.8 million people."},{"time":224642,"text":"Now it's at this time that Detroit begins to see"},{"time":227020,"text":"a second kind of migration,"},{"time":229238,"text":"a migration to the suburbs."},{"time":231571,"text":"Between 1950 and 2000,"},{"time":234408,"text":"the region grows by 30 percent."},{"time":237343,"text":"But this time, the migration leaves"},{"time":239242,"text":"African-Americans in place,"},{"time":241347,"text":"as families and businesses flee the city,"},{"time":244293,"text":"leaving the city pretty desolate of people"},{"time":246655,"text":"as well as jobs."},{"time":248409,"text":"During that same period, between\n1950 and 2000, 2010,"},{"time":253209,"text":"the city loses 60 percent of its population,"},{"time":256074,"text":"and today it hovers at above 700,000."}]},{"cues":[{"time":259998,"text":"The audience members who come\nand talk to us that night"},{"time":262484,"text":"tell us the stories of what it's like to live in a city"},{"time":265269,"text":"with such depleted population."},{"time":267986,"text":"Many tell us that they're one of only a few homes"},{"time":270336,"text":"on their block that are occupied,"},{"time":272879,"text":"and that they can see several abandoned homes"},{"time":275486,"text":"from where they sit on their porches."},{"time":277733,"text":"Citywide, there are 80,000 vacant homes."},{"time":282072,"text":"They can also see vacant property."},{"time":285087,"text":"They're beginning to see illegal activities"},{"time":286944,"text":"on these properties, like illegal dumping,"},{"time":289168,"text":"and they know that because the city\nhas lost so much population,"},{"time":293473,"text":"their costs for water, electricity, gas are rising,"},{"time":298640,"text":"because there are not enough people\nto pay property taxes"},{"time":301482,"text":"to help support the services that they need."},{"time":304816,"text":"Citywide, there are about 100,000 vacant parcels."}]},{"cues":[{"time":309073,"text":"Now, to quickly give you all a sense of a scale,"},{"time":311067,"text":"because I know that sounds like a big number,"},{"time":312417,"text":"but I don't think you quite understand\nuntil you look at the city map."},{"time":314955,"text":"So the city is 139 square miles."},{"time":317661,"text":"You can fit Boston, San Francisco,"},{"time":319707,"text":"and the island of Manhattan"},{"time":321267,"text":"within its footprint."},{"time":322943,"text":"So if we take all of that vacant\nand abandoned property"},{"time":325333,"text":"and we smush it together,"},{"time":327529,"text":"it looks like about 20 square miles,"},{"time":329365,"text":"and that's roughly equivalent to the size"},{"time":331333,"text":"of the island we're sitting on today, Manhattan,"},{"time":333040,"text":"at 22 square miles."},{"time":334490,"text":"So it's a lot of vacancy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":338090,"text":"Now some of our audience members"},{"time":340266,"text":"also tell us about some of the positive things"},{"time":342384,"text":"that are happening in their communities,"},{"time":344429,"text":"and many of them are banding together"},{"time":346016,"text":"to take control of some of the vacant lots,"},{"time":348122,"text":"and they're starting community gardens,"},{"time":349991,"text":"which are creating a great sense\nof community stewardship,"},{"time":352666,"text":"but they're very, very clear to tell us"},{"time":354661,"text":"that this is not enough,"},{"time":356452,"text":"that they want to see their neighborhoods"},{"time":357958,"text":"return to the way that their\ngrandparents had found them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":361311,"text":"Now there's been a lot of speculation since 2010"},{"time":363754,"text":"about what to do with the vacant property,"},{"time":366430,"text":"and a lot of that speculation has\nbeen around community gardening,"},{"time":369150,"text":"or what we call urban agriculture."},{"time":371382,"text":"So many people would say to us,"},{"time":372960,"text":"\"What if you just take all that vacant land\nand you could make it farmland?"},{"time":375668,"text":"It can provide fresh foods,"},{"time":377771,"text":"and it can put Detroiters back to work too.\""},{"time":380476,"text":"When I hear that story,"},{"time":381921,"text":"I always imagine the folks from the Great Migration"},{"time":384537,"text":"rolling over in their graves,"},{"time":386791,"text":"because you can imagine that they didn't sacrifice"},{"time":390108,"text":"moving from the South to the North"},{"time":392185,"text":"to create a better life for their families,"},{"time":394297,"text":"only to see their great-grandchildren\nreturn to an agrarian lifestyle,"},{"time":398543,"text":"especially in a city where they came"},{"time":400751,"text":"with little less than a high school education"},{"time":402805,"text":"or even a grammar school education"},{"time":404772,"text":"and were able to afford the basic elements"},{"time":406797,"text":"of the American dream:"},{"time":408086,"text":"steady work and a home that they owned."}]},{"cues":[{"time":412121,"text":"Now, there's a third wave of migration"},{"time":414352,"text":"happening in Detroit:"},{"time":415912,"text":"a new ascendant of cultural entrepreneurs."},{"time":419056,"text":"These folks see that same vacant land"},{"time":421472,"text":"and those same abandoned homes"},{"time":422967,"text":"as opportunity for new,"},{"time":424362,"text":"entrepreneurial ideas and profit,"},{"time":427033,"text":"so much so that former models"},{"time":429020,"text":"can move to Detroit,"},{"time":430441,"text":"buy property, start successful"},{"time":432762,"text":"businesses and restaurants,"},{"time":434439,"text":"and become successful community\nactivists in their neighborhood,"},{"time":437419,"text":"bringing about very positive change."},{"time":440441,"text":"Similarly, we have small manufacturing companies"},{"time":443345,"text":"making conscious decisions to relocate to the city."},{"time":446614,"text":"This company, Shinola, which is a luxury watch"},{"time":449399,"text":"and bicycle company,"},{"time":451111,"text":"deliberately chose to relocate to Detroit,"},{"time":453004,"text":"and they quote themselves by saying"},{"time":455641,"text":"they were drawn to the global brand \nof Detroit's innovation."},{"time":459899,"text":"And they also knew that \nthey can tap into a workforce"},{"time":462471,"text":"that was still very skilled in how to make things."},{"time":465997,"text":"Now we have community stewardship\n"},{"time":468566,"text":"happening in neighborhoods,"},{"time":470126,"text":"we have cultural entrepreneurs making decisions"},{"time":472925,"text":"to move to the city and create enterprises,"},{"time":475973,"text":"and we have businesses relocating,"},{"time":477708,"text":"and this is all in the context"},{"time":479094,"text":"of what is no secret to us all,"},{"time":481366,"text":"a city that's under the control"},{"time":483167,"text":"of an emergency manager,"},{"time":484789,"text":"and just this July filed for Chapter 9 bankruptcy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":489063,"text":"So 2010, we started this process, and by 2013,"},{"time":492305,"text":"we released Detroit Future City,"},{"time":494389,"text":"which was our strategic plan to guide the city"},{"time":497227,"text":"into a better and more prosperous"},{"time":499046,"text":"and more sustainable existence --"},{"time":501323,"text":"not what it was, but what it could be,"},{"time":504988,"text":"looking at new ways of economic growth,"},{"time":508303,"text":"new forms of land use,"},{"time":510284,"text":"more sustainable and denser neighborhoods,"},{"time":513392,"text":"a reconfigured infrastructure\nand city service system,"},{"time":516808,"text":"and a heightened capacity for civic leaders"},{"time":519676,"text":"to take action and implement change."},{"time":522938,"text":"Three key imperatives were really important"},{"time":525536,"text":"to our work."},{"time":526817,"text":"One was that the city itself\nwasn't necessarily too large,"},{"time":530695,"text":"but the economy was too small."},{"time":532383,"text":"There are only 27 jobs per 100 people in Detroit,"},{"time":535643,"text":"very different from a Denver\nor an Atlanta or a Philadelphia"},{"time":539041,"text":"that are anywhere between \n35 to 70 jobs per 100 people."},{"time":543961,"text":"Secondly, there had to be an acceptance"},{"time":546383,"text":"that we were not going to be able to use"},{"time":548339,"text":"all of this vacant land in the way that we had before"},{"time":551203,"text":"and maybe for some time to come."},{"time":553212,"text":"It wasn't going to be our traditional\nresidential neighborhoods"},{"time":555777,"text":"as we had before,"},{"time":557394,"text":"and urban agriculture, while a very productive"},{"time":560152,"text":"and successful intervention happening in Detroit,"},{"time":562844,"text":"was not the only answer,"},{"time":564947,"text":"that what we had to do is look at these areas"},{"time":567383,"text":"where we had significant vacancy"},{"time":569191,"text":"but still had a significant number of population"},{"time":572426,"text":"of what could be new, productive, innovative,"},{"time":575324,"text":"and entrepreneurial uses"},{"time":576858,"text":"that could stabilize those communities,"},{"time":578813,"text":"where still nearly 300,000 residents lived."}]},{"cues":[{"time":582181,"text":"So we came up with one neighborhood typology --"},{"time":584997,"text":"there are several --\ncalled a live-make neighborhood,"},{"time":587970,"text":"where folks could reappropriate"},{"time":589929,"text":"abandoned structures"},{"time":591667,"text":"and turn them into entrepreneurial enterprises,"},{"time":593957,"text":"with a specific emphasis on looking at the, again,"},{"time":597040,"text":"majority 82 percent African-American population."},{"time":600225,"text":"So they, too, could take businesses"},{"time":602326,"text":"that they maybe were doing out of their home"},{"time":604725,"text":"and grow them to more prosperous industries"},{"time":607436,"text":"and actually acquire property so they were actually"},{"time":610146,"text":"property owners as well as business owners"},{"time":612595,"text":"in the communities with which they resided."},{"time":615121,"text":"Then we also wanted to look at other ways"},{"time":617199,"text":"of using land in addition to growing food"},{"time":620533,"text":"and transforming landscape into"},{"time":622357,"text":"much more productive uses,"},{"time":624217,"text":"so that it could be used for storm\nwater management, for example,"},{"time":627507,"text":"by using surface lakes and retention ponds,"},{"time":630523,"text":"that created neighborhood amenities,"},{"time":632283,"text":"places of recreation,"},{"time":633975,"text":"and actually helped to elevate"},{"time":635792,"text":"adjacent property levels."},{"time":637479,"text":"Or we could use it as research plots,"},{"time":639339,"text":"where we can use it to remediate contaminated soils,"},{"time":642647,"text":"or we could use it to generate energy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":646613,"text":"So the descendants of the Great Migration"},{"time":649811,"text":"could either become precision\nwatchmakers at Shinola,"},{"time":653055,"text":"like Willie H., who was featured\nin one of their ads last year,"},{"time":656366,"text":"or they can actually grow a business"},{"time":658758,"text":"that would service companies like Shinola."},{"time":661483,"text":"The good news is, there is a future"},{"time":663485,"text":"for the next generation of Detroiters,"},{"time":666044,"text":"both those there now and those that want to come."}]},{"cues":[{"time":669208,"text":"So no thank you, Mayor Menino,"},{"time":671339,"text":"who recently was quoted as saying,"},{"time":672982,"text":"\"I'd blow up the place and start over.\""},{"time":675597,"text":"There are very important people,"},{"time":677948,"text":"business and land assets in Detroit,"},{"time":680349,"text":"and there are real opportunities there."},{"time":682145,"text":"So while Detroit might not be what it was,"},{"time":684768,"text":"Detroit will not die."}]},{"cues":[{"time":686387,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":688410,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}